{"name": "cds-302-project", "metadata": {"name": "cds-302-project", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pathlib", "python-dotenv", "sqlalchemy", "pandas", "logging", "sqlalchemy-utils", "argparse", "openpyxl"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1732429745}, "documentation": ["# SPEats - Meal Planning and Recipe Management App\n\nA Python application for meal planning and recipe management.\n\n## Description\n\nSPEats is a meal planning and recipe management application. It allows users to manage recipes, plan meals, and interact with a database of dishes and ingredients.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall the required dependencies using Poetry:\n\n```sh\npoetry install\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nRun the application using the main.py script:\n\n```sh\npython cds_302_project/main.py\n```\n\nUse the `--drop-tables` flag to drop existing tables before creating new ones.\n\n## Modules\n\n- main.py: The main program that initializes and runs the application.\n- db.py: Contains database models and setup.\n- config.py: Defines paths to directories and configuration settings.\n- data_handler.py: Reads data from Excel and populates the database.\n\n## Configuration\n\nConfiguration settings are defined in config.py. Environment variables are loaded from the `.env` file, which contains database credentials.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDependencies are managed using Poetry and specified in `pyproject.toml`. Key dependencies include:\n\n- `sqlalchemy`\n- `pandas`\n- `python-dotenv`\n- `argparse`\n\n## Project Information\n\nThis project was developed as part of the CDS 302 (Scientific Data and Databases) course at George Mason University Korea.\n\n**Group Members:**\n\n- Tyson Johnson (<tjohns94@gmu.edu>)\n- Giselle Rahimi (<grahimi@gmu.edu>)\n- Woohyun Song (<wsong8@gmu.edu>)\n- Juheon Kim (<jkim314@gmu.edu>)\n\n**Professor:** Dr. John K. Leung\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License:\n\n```\nMIT License\n\nCopyright (c) 2024\nTyson Johnson <tjohns94@gmu.edu>,\nGiselle Rahimi <grahimi@gmu.edu>,\nWoohyun Song <wsong8@gmu.edu>,\nJuheon Kim <jkim314@gmu.edu>\n\nPermission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal in the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software...\n```"], "modules": [{"name": "cds_302_project.main", "documentation": ["SPEats - a meal planning and recipe management app\n\nModules:\n- main.py: main program\n- db.py: database models and setup\n- config.py: paths to directories and configuration settings\n- data_handler.py: reads data from Excel and populates the database\n\nTo run the program, execute main.py in the terminal.\n\n=======================\n\nAuthor: Tyson Johnson\nDate: 2024-06-25\nVersion: 1.0"], "functions": [{"name": "cds_302_project.main.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "drop_tables", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "cds_302_project.main.parser", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cds_302_project.main.args", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cds_302_project", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cds_302_project.data_handler", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "cds_302_project.data_handler.DataHandler", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "cds_302_project.data_handler.DataHandler.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "entry_file", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}